{
  "texts": [
    "If a voter knows that their candidate has virtually no chance of winning, they can choose to simply disregard this option, which eliminates one portion of the options set and very much simplifies voting choice.",
    "We conclude that AI polls contribute to core voter knowledge in a more effective way than traditional survey methods by increasing the granularity and frequency of strategic knowledge.",
    "Coming back to the example of the UK voter, your (revised) core voter question is: \"Which candidate would be better by my lights who has a chance of winning?\"",
    "(Dummett 1997) Under traditional polling, you would have been misled to vote tactically for the LibDem (wasting your first preference for Labour).",
    "In reality, the LibDems' chances of victory were significantly lower than what the traditional poll hypothesised."
  ]
}